13 Sec. 2. 1. The Subcommittee created by section 1.9 of this
14 act shall study:
15 (a) The economic, political, social, educational and historical
16 impacts of slavery, Jim Crow laws, de jure and de facto racial
17 segregation and other forms of racial discrimination in the State of
18 Nevada, as well as the prior organized and unorganized territories
19 that constitute a part of the current state boundaries of the State;
20 (b) Discriminatory habits or practices, including, without
21 limitation, forced slavery, chattel slavery, indentured servitude,
22 redlining, segregated school systems and segregated public goods
23 and spaces, that may have caused significant economic or societal
24 disparities of formerly enslaved Africans or their descendants; and
25 (c) The related economic effects to present day society in the
26 State of Nevada as a result of the matters studied pursuant to this
27 subsection.
28 2. On or before August 31, 2026, the Subcommittee shall
29 present its findings and make recommendations, including specific
